Results of modern investigations of microphysical and optical characteristics of atmospheric aerosol are systematized; calculation methods are presented, and a number of original numerical investigations of vertical stratification of optical-radar parameters of continental aerosol are realized.
Data calculations embrace a wide spectral band of visible and infrared radiation.
Examples and recommendations for practical use of model assessments are given.
